‚Ä¢ As a creator or someone working in Web3, it‚Äôs good to always pay attention to projects and the offer they are giving you. Especially the ones offering to pay in tokens with no expected date for TGE. 

‚Ä¢ If I had taken the deal, I‚Äôd have been working for 2yrs without pay üòÇ

‚Ä¢ Always stick to upfront payment, on a worst case scenario accept 50% upfront and the remaining after the job. 

‚Ä¢ If a project really need your services, they will pay.

DeFi lending and borrowing protocols thrive, but lack one thing, Fixed Rates, the volatility of crypto prevents this.
 
But guess what? @termslabs is fixing this.
 
Term Finance is a decentralized fixed-rate lending protocol designed to bring predictability to DeFi.  
 
With terms finance dealing with fluctuating rates, borrowers lock in fixed costs, and lenders secure stable returns.
 
Why does fixed-rate lending matter in DeFi?
 
Most DeFi lending protocols today run on floating rates, meaning, borrowers and lenders are at the mercy of market swings.
 
Term Finance changes that with fixed-rate lending through an on-chain auction system ensuring, borrowers know their interest costs upfront.  
Lenders earn predictable, stable yields.  
No slippage or inefficiencies.  

How Term Finance borrows from TradFi
 
TradFi has long relied on fixed-rate lending for stability
Term Finance brings that to DeFi with:  

‚óè Fixed-rate borrowing (like mortgages & bonds).  
‚óè Auction-based price discovery, similar to government bond sales.  
‚óè On-chain transparency, ensuring trustless execution.  
 
What makes Term Finance different from traditional finance ?  
 
Unlike Automated Market Maker AMM-based lending protocols, Term Finance is built for efficiency and scalability. With on-chain auctions, it matches:
 
1Ô∏è‚É£ Borrowers/lenders at a single market-clearing rate.
 
2Ô∏è‚É£ Capital efficiency: Funds are locked only during auctions, freeing up liquidity.
 
3Ô∏è‚É£ Non-custodial: You stay in control, no middleman.
 
4Ô∏è‚É£ Fixed rates: No more rate volatility headaches.  

 Round Up
Term Finance is bringing fixed-rate stability to DeFi lending. With it's auction-based system, transparent execution, and TradFi-inspired efficiency, it's changing the borrowing and lending landscape of DeFi.
